HEADWORD: Daint
<hw>Daint</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Dainty</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>Something of exquisite taste; a dainty.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> -- <def2><pos>a.</pos> <def>Dainty.</def></def2>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To cherish him with diets <qex>daint</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Daintify</ent>⟦br⟧
